WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.999
MARISHA: And I cast my Skywrite spell-- ew, I just
spit-- and I use the smoke in the distance and as

00:00:08.046 --> 00:00:16.309
it's rising up into the sky, start drawing out the
de Rolo family crest in the smoke.

00:00:16.309 --> 00:00:22.645
MATT: Okay. You begin to take the plume of smoke
and filter into the dark rain clouds and you make

00:00:22.645 --> 00:00:28.295
the smoke go to a thicker, thicker black and take
the next few moments to begin sculpting in the air

00:00:28.338 --> 00:00:32.750
until eventually we have a very well-defined de
Rolo crest now staring down at the entire city of

00:00:32.750 --> 00:00:34.008
Whitestone.

00:00:34.008 --> 00:00:37.293
SAM: Oh! Something's happening! Something's
happening in the sky!

00:00:37.293 --> 00:00:38.700
MARISHA: That's me.

00:00:38.700 --> 00:00:43.252
SAM: I think it's a magic wielder of some sort.
Something-- I must flee!

00:00:43.252 --> 00:00:46.311
(laughter)

00:00:46.311 --> 00:00:53.239
MATT: All right. Investigation checks from both of
you.

00:00:53.239 --> 00:00:55.071
LAURA: Okay.

00:00:55.071 --> 00:00:57.349
TRAVIS: Did I find anything on Smash-Face?

00:00:57.349 --> 00:00:59.510
LIAM: (sighs) That's what you rolled the last
time.

00:00:59.510 --> 00:01:00.523
LAURA: I know!

00:01:00.523 --> 00:01:01.719
TALIESIN: 16.

00:01:01.719 --> 00:01:03.194
LAURA: I've got to put this one away for a while.

00:01:03.194 --> 00:01:04.329
MATT: What did you roll?

00:01:04.329 --> 00:01:06.680
LAURA: I rolled a nine.

00:01:06.680 --> 00:01:13.059
MATT: Okay. The two of you take a while upstairs
looking about the rooms. You manage to acquire

00:01:13.128 --> 00:01:20.877
from just some of the local bits of cabinets and
dust, you gather about 230 gold pieces.

00:01:20.877 --> 00:01:22.292
LAURA: 230?

00:01:22.292 --> 00:01:27.191
MATT: Just loose gold pieces that are around.
There is a nice jewelry box that seems to contain

00:01:27.191 --> 00:01:31.314
most of the jewels and gems that this individual
likes.

00:01:31.314 --> 00:01:33.430
LAURA: I'm going to take the whole jewelry box and
sort through it later.

00:01:33.430 --> 00:01:38.539
MATT: Okay. So say a box of Tylieri's jewelry
would be what you've marked down.

00:01:38.539 --> 00:01:40.349
TALIESIN: Tylieri family jewels.

00:01:40.349 --> 00:01:42.113
(laughter)

00:01:42.113 --> 00:01:43.431
TALIESIN: That won't be confusing at all.

00:01:43.431 --> 00:01:46.716
MATT: There you go. You do notice, however, that's
all you're able to find for the most part, other than

00:01:46.716 --> 00:01:51.111
some few bits of clothing and outfit. The master
bedroom has no bed.

00:01:51.178 --> 00:01:54.477
LAURA: Does he sleep in a coffin?

00:01:54.477 --> 00:01:58.175
TALIESIN: We're going to finish searching
downstairs and then find the entrance to the--

00:01:58.175 --> 00:01:59.475
MATT: Okay.

00:01:59.475 --> 00:02:02.712
LIAM: I'd like to wind my way up there, as well.

00:02:02.712 --> 00:02:05.390
MATT: Okay, as you make your way up there you
notice them stepping out.

00:02:05.390 --> 00:02:08.316
LIAM: Yeah. I'm still curious. I want to go have a
look as well.

00:02:08.316 --> 00:02:09.986
MATT: Go for it. Investigation.

00:02:09.986 --> 00:02:11.477
LAURA: That's better, thank you.

00:02:11.477 --> 00:02:13.307
LIAM: 16.

00:02:13.307 --> 00:02:17.779
MATT: 16? You look through the room. Most
everything of interest has already been picked

00:02:17.779 --> 00:02:24.586
clean. This room also doesn't seem to see much use
other than the clothing that's in there. This room

00:02:24.586 --> 00:02:28.202
is used for dressing and presentational purposes
but other than that, as a bedroom, it's pretty

00:02:28.202 --> 00:02:34.957
useless. As you guys go downstairs, we'll say for
the sake of brevity you take a little bit of time

00:02:34.957 --> 00:02:38.249
to start looking through. You know you're a little
pressed for time because you can feel the energy

00:02:38.249 --> 00:02:41.176
in the town begin to rise and you start hearing
noises. You keeping an eye out?

00:02:41.176 --> 00:02:42.148
MARISHA: Yeah.

00:02:42.148 --> 00:02:44.728
MATT: The people that rush into the rooms are now
rushing back out, some of them wearing leather

00:02:44.728 --> 00:02:49.317
tunics and small bits of armor, their weapons
gathered, and they're forming small bands.

00:02:49.317 --> 00:02:54.808
MARISHA: I come over the speakers once again, the
ear pieces. "I think it's time to go. Whenever you

00:02:54.808 --> 00:02:57.007
"guys are ready, I want to light this bitch up."

00:02:57.007 --> 00:02:59.452
TRAVIS: We need to check all the rooms that go
downstairs first.

00:02:59.452 --> 00:03:00.750
MARISHA: All right, quick.

00:03:00.750 --> 00:03:05.756
TRAVIS: "Got an empty house." I run out to the
door to the left. To the uncovered areas.

00:03:05.756 --> 00:03:10.710
MATT: Okay. You go over to this hallway. You
eventually smash the door, doesn't take too long.

00:03:10.710 --> 00:03:19.657
It leads into what looks like a small study or
some sort of an office room. A big blue rug, a

00:03:19.657 --> 00:03:22.318
desk with a chair, some papers strewn about.

00:03:22.318 --> 00:03:24.772
TRAVIS: Can I grab the rug and yank it?

00:03:24.772 --> 00:03:27.239
MATT: Yeah, pull the rug off, reveals a hatch.

00:03:27.239 --> 00:03:29.421
TRAVIS: (excited shouting) I found a hatch!

00:03:29.421 --> 00:03:32.540
LAURA: (cries out in pain) No need to yell!

00:03:32.540 --> 00:03:34.628
TRAVIS: Oh sorry. (quieter) I found a hatch.

00:03:34.628 --> 00:03:38.690
TALIESIN: Quick, I just want to do a quick round
of the downstairs room before going to the hatch.

00:03:38.690 --> 00:03:43.490
MATT: Okay. Glancing about, you find what looks to
be a general sitting area, a music room, or a

00:03:43.490 --> 00:03:49.769
place where you would host guests. Also in fair disuse.
And then beyond that, you find a room that's

00:03:49.769 --> 00:03:55.494
pretty bland, with a staircase that leads down
into what was once servants' quarters that has

00:03:55.494 --> 00:03:57.209
been converted into a torture room.

00:03:57.209 --> 00:03:58.649
LAURA: Oh, lovely.

00:03:58.649 --> 00:04:04.368
MATT: It's a little nicer in its presentation and
tools than the duergar torture room that you

00:04:04.368 --> 00:04:10.348
encountered in the Underdark, but this looks to be
like Tylieri had a definite interest in

00:04:10.348 --> 00:04:14.970
entertaining unwanted guests.

00:04:14.970 --> 00:04:16.685
TALIESIN: Okay.

00:04:16.685 --> 00:04:20.499
TRAVIS: Vax or Vex, will you come check this hatch
for boobies?

00:04:20.499 --> 00:04:22.438
(laughter)

00:04:22.438 --> 00:04:24.236
LIAM: I jog on down.

00:04:24.236 --> 00:04:26.549
MATT: All right, make a perception check.

00:04:26.549 --> 00:04:30.079
LIAM: Yeah. That's a 23.

00:04:30.079 --> 00:04:32.179
MATT: Yeah, it does not appear to be trapped.

00:04:32.179 --> 00:04:33.449
TRAVIS: No boobies.

00:04:33.449 --> 00:04:35.317
LIAM: Okay. You want to open that, big guy?

00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:37.701
TRAVIS: Yeah! (growls)

00:04:37.753 --> 00:04:44.923
MATT: (vroom) The hatch comes up. There is no
ladder; it's just a ten-foot drop down into a

00:04:44.923 --> 00:04:45.879
basement.

00:04:45.879 --> 00:04:47.242
TRAVIS: Okay, I jump.

00:04:47.242 --> 00:04:52.750
MATT: Land down there. A 20 foot by 20 foot room.
It's very musty. However, you do see in the far

00:04:52.750 --> 00:04:57.718
corner there is a pad of fresh earth set up, and
there is a dark box.

00:04:57.718 --> 00:04:59.414
TRAVIS: Um.

00:04:59.414 --> 00:05:00.653
MATT: About eight feet long.

00:05:00.653 --> 00:05:04.090
LIAM: I hear him say "Um," and I jump down, too.
With the Flametongue dagger out for light.

00:05:04.090 --> 00:05:08.456
MATT: Okay. The room lights up a little bit and
you can see across the way there is a not

00:05:08.504 --> 00:05:12.255
super-detailed, but a fairly well-crafted coffin
on the opposite side of the room.

00:05:12.255 --> 00:05:16.196
TRAVIS: Ooh! I bet there's treasure in there!

00:05:16.196 --> 00:05:19.243
LIAM: You might be right. Yeah, let's go have a
look.

00:05:19.303 --> 00:05:21.028
LAURA: Is there treasure? Did you find treasure?

00:05:21.028 --> 00:05:27.407
LIAM: "Hold, please." Perception check the coffin.
That's a 20.

00:05:27.407 --> 00:05:32.249
MATT: Okay. The coffin does not appear to be
trapped?

00:05:32.249 --> 00:05:34.186
TRAVIS: Can I open it?

00:05:34.186 --> 00:05:35.924
MARISHA: He said that with a question mark.

00:05:35.924 --> 00:05:37.645
MATT: It's always fun to do that.

00:05:37.645 --> 00:05:41.659
TRAVIS: Well, should I just smash it?

00:05:41.659 --> 00:05:43.984
LIAM: I really feel like this could be--

00:05:43.984 --> 00:05:45.261
LAURA: Smash it!

00:05:45.261 --> 00:05:50.549
TRAVIS: Three, two. Grog smashes.

00:05:50.549 --> 00:05:53.908
LIAM: I kick it off with the end of my foot.
Little bit. Or try to.

00:05:53.908 --> 00:06:00.116
MATT: Okay. (boof) The lid flies off and then
slams on the ground. A smell hits you that's just

00:06:00.116 --> 00:06:08.678
like musty old mildewed earth. The inside of the
coffin is, it's lined with like a fine purplish

00:06:08.678 --> 00:06:13.748
velvet material, the smell quickly fades. It looks
like there are some small baubles in there,

00:06:13.748 --> 00:06:22.248
keepsakes. There is what looks to be a cape or a
cloak that is laid across the bottom of this for

00:06:22.248 --> 00:06:24.061
comfort.

00:06:24.133 --> 00:06:28.729
LIAM: Roll it up. Put it into my satchel. I'm
going to take a dagger out and I want to cut all

00:06:28.814 --> 00:06:32.428
the way up through that purple velvet. Just see,
just in case.

00:06:32.428 --> 00:06:36.840
MATT: Okay. You cut through the purple velvet.
Rummage through underneath. It appears to be the

00:06:36.840 --> 00:06:39.169
back of the box.

00:06:39.169 --> 00:06:41.723
TALIESIN: I'm going to check his desk upstairs for
anything interesting.

00:06:41.723 --> 00:06:45.339
MATT: Okay. Want to make an investigation check?

00:06:45.339 --> 00:06:47.958
TALIESIN: Natural 20.

00:06:47.958 --> 00:06:56.119
MATT: As you're rummaging through the notes in the
desk, a lot of them are ledgers involving the

00:06:56.119 --> 00:07:00.058
trade in and out of the city. He has his hands
dabbling in elements of the timber trade, elements

00:07:00.058 --> 00:07:08.135
of the actual trade of whitestone. He talks about
the-- and you understand, the reason that

00:07:08.135 --> 00:07:13.735
Whitestone itself is-- the stone that's mined here
is so popular for construction and architecture

00:07:13.735 --> 00:07:22.295
and other elements is the stone that these
mountains are made of, when properly prepared,

00:07:22.295 --> 00:07:28.851
there is a faint bit of residuum that is naturally
ingrained in the rock here. No one really knows

00:07:28.851 --> 00:07:33.972
how it came about, but whatever it is, while it is
not inherently magical, it makes it a little bit

00:07:33.972 --> 00:07:38.876
easier, faster, and cheaper to enchant the stone.
So when it comes to, you know, enchanting a

00:07:38.876 --> 00:07:46.172
teleportation circle permanently somewhere or for
traps or things-- not actual objects but actually

00:07:46.212 --> 00:07:52.081
enchanting anything made of stonework. It's easier
to enchant, and that's why the whitestone of this

00:07:52.081 --> 00:07:58.182
area is sought after and a good trade element. So
there's notes about that. But the stone trade has

00:07:58.182 --> 00:08:03.271
been halted, all stone has continued to be mined,
but it's not being transported.

00:08:03.271 --> 00:08:06.022
TRAVIS: Is the desk made out of the stone?

00:08:06.070 --> 00:08:12.451
MATT: No, there's just notes about it. So all the
whitestone that is being mined is not being

00:08:12.451 --> 00:08:14.731
exported. It's being kept here, somewhere.

00:08:14.731 --> 00:08:15.887
LAURA: They're making something big.

00:08:15.887 --> 00:08:17.149
TALIESIN: They're making something big.

00:08:17.149 --> 00:08:19.562
LIAM: I think we need to get out of here.

00:08:19.562 --> 00:08:21.969
TRAVIS: I was going to ask, are you good with the
coffin?

00:08:21.969 --> 00:08:24.321
LIAM: Yeah.

00:08:24.321 --> 00:08:27.842
TRAVIS: Okay. I smash the shit out of it, in an
effort to see what's underneath.

00:08:27.900 --> 00:08:33.746
MATT: Okay. You take about 30 seconds of extreme
violence against the wooden coffin, killing it

00:08:33.746 --> 00:08:39.347
into chunks and blocks. You get the feeling that
this may have been the place the mist was

00:08:39.347 --> 00:08:50.111
trying to get to. But it did not make its journey.
It got scattered by druid Sunbeam and destroyed,

00:08:50.165 --> 00:08:56.452
and the coffin is left in ruins. You do-- even you,
Grog-- absorb the fact that when a vampire goes to

00:08:56.452 --> 00:09:01.232
mist form, you get the feeling that this is the
home it needs to come to, to try and survive.

00:09:01.322 --> 00:09:03.123
TRAVIS: Not anymore.

00:09:03.123 --> 00:09:04.902
MATT: Not anymore. Not that one.

00:09:04.902 --> 00:09:07.775
MARISHA: Do I see anyone coming?

00:09:07.775 --> 00:09:13.371
MATT: Oh. You see another zombie giant coming up
the way. You can see people attacking it, it's

00:09:13.371 --> 00:09:16.849
just thrashing them about, but this one seems less
bothered by the group and is now moving towards a

00:09:16.849 --> 00:09:21.921
specific area, moving towards the fiery plume
in the distance. They're all gathering in that

00:09:22.010 --> 00:09:22.876
direction.

00:09:22.876 --> 00:09:24.430
MARISHA: But no one seems to be rushing towards
this house?

00:09:24.430 --> 00:09:25.446
MATT: Not at the moment, no.

00:09:25.446 --> 00:09:27.047
TRAVIS: This one's not on fire. Yet.

00:09:27.047 --> 00:09:34.228
MATT: All right, you all gather, you can hear the
rainstorm itself is coming down in sheets. What

00:09:34.263 --> 00:09:35.467
do you want to do?

00:09:35.467 --> 00:09:36.861
TRAVIS: Light this candle!

00:09:36.861 --> 00:09:38.599
LAURA: Should we light this on fire, too?

00:09:38.599 --> 00:09:40.224
TALIESIN: Burn it to the ground.

00:09:40.224 --> 00:09:44.394
MARISHA: "Everyone out." And I start casting a
Flaming Sphere.

00:09:44.394 --> 00:09:45.635
MATT: Okay.

00:09:45.635 --> 00:09:46.876
TRAVIS: We're out by now.

00:09:46.876 --> 00:09:48.002
MARISHA: Everyone out.

00:09:48.002 --> 00:09:51.765
MATT: You guys all step out into the rain
(whooshes) pouring down. What bits of guard blood

00:09:51.765 --> 00:09:53.965
that have been pressed against you washes off.

00:09:53.965 --> 00:09:55.174
TRAVIS: Aw.

00:09:55.174 --> 00:10:01.784
MARISHA: I peek in this foyer. And just (boof),
right in the middle, and take a minute to

00:10:01.784 --> 00:10:03.710
move it all around.

00:10:03.767 --> 00:10:07.643
MATT: A Flaming Sphere begins to corkscrew around
this room, up over the banister, up to the upper

00:10:07.643 --> 00:10:13.227
area, and like an artist, you paint this entire
room with flame until the entire interior of this

00:10:13.227 --> 00:10:18.664
main foyer is just an inferno. You can hear the
flames licking and the light is very bright. You

00:10:18.664 --> 00:10:24.172
end up backing up and you can see people,
unarmored folk in nearby homes that are pressed up

00:10:24.172 --> 00:10:28.851
against their windows watching this happen and
whispering to each other. The children, those that

00:10:28.851 --> 00:10:33.065
are kept guarded and are not part of this
rebellion, they are watching this with smiles.

00:10:33.065 --> 00:10:38.084
MARISHA: Okay, I think that's good enough.
Let's go.

00:10:38.148 --> 00:10:40.109
TALIESIN: Head back to the curiosity shop.

00:10:40.109 --> 00:10:42.204
LAURA: Yeah, sneaky, stealthing.

00:10:42.204 --> 00:10:44.647
MATT: Okay. As you guys run off into the alley
behind--

00:10:44.647 --> 00:10:46.474
LAURA: Pass Without a Trace I cast on all of us.

00:10:46.474 --> 00:10:50.665
MATT: Okay. How many more spells do you have at
that level? Because you used it several times

00:10:50.665 --> 00:10:51.594
today.

00:10:51.594 --> 00:10:55.286
LAURA: Yeah, I'm fine with Pass Without a Trace.
That's a 1st-level. 2nd-level, but I'm fine.

00:10:55.286 --> 00:10:56.736
TALIESIN: Back to the alcove, then?

00:10:56.736 --> 00:11:02.035
MATT: You guys all dart off into the alley under
the cover of the shadows of the storm and the

00:11:02.035 --> 00:11:05.004
rainfall, to head towards the alcove, and we'll go
ahead and take a quick break.

00:11:05.004 --> 00:11:06.535
(cheering)

00:11:06.535 --> 00:11:08.982
MATT: A quick break, I know I always say that, I'm
not going to say five minutes, but.

00:11:08.982 --> 00:11:10.218
SAM: This one's a real quick break.

00:11:10.218 --> 00:11:11.745
MATT: We'll take it real quick because we want to
try and get through as much of the story before we

00:11:11.745 --> 00:11:13.293
get to Critmas.

00:11:13.293 --> 00:11:14.215
LAURA: Critmas!

00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:15.245
LIAM: Critmas! Crimmas.

00:11:15.245 --> 00:11:16.246
TALIESIN: Oh dear god.

00:11:16.246 --> 00:11:17.116
TRAVIS: It's going to be a thing.

00:11:17.116 --> 00:11:18.293
MATT: Which is going to, which is going to take
some time tonight. Be back here in a few minutes

00:11:18.293 --> 00:11:19.275
guys, we'll see you in a sec.

00:11:19.275 --> 00:11:20.046
TRAVIS: Pizza!

00:11:20.046 --> 00:25:30.878
[break]

